     1# BMAD METHOD - Generic Project Template
     2
     3## Overview
     4The **Build Management Automation & Deployment (BMAD) METHOD** is a context-preserved development framework that can be deployed to any software project to enhance development workflows, maintain context across sessions, and automate planning and deployment processes.
     5
     6## Core Architecture
     7
     8### Directory Structure
     9```
    10.bmad/
    11 config/
    12    bmad-config.json          # Project-specific configuration
    13    file-patterns.json        # File inclusion/exclusion patterns
    14    deployment-targets.json   # Deployment environment configs
    15 agents/
    16    generic-agents/           # Reusable agent templates
    17       architecture-agent.json
    18       deployment-agent.json
    19       testing-agent.json
    20       security-agent.json
    21    project-agents/          # Project-specific agents
    22 stories/
    23    active/                  # Current development stories
    24    completed/               # Completed stories archive
    25    templates/              # Story templates by type
    26 context/
    27    project-context.xml     # Flattened codebase context
    28    architecture.json       # System architecture snapshot
    29    dependencies.json       # Dependency analysis
    30 workflows/
    31    bmad-quickstart.md      # Getting started guide
    32    deployment-workflows/    # Deployment procedures
    33    testing-workflows/      # Testing automation
    34 scripts/
    35     bmad-init.js            # Project initialization
    36     codebase-flattener.js   # Context generation
    37     story-generator.js      # Story creation
    38     agent-planner.js        # Multi-agent planning
    39     deploy-with-context.js  # Context-aware deployment
    40```
    41
    42## Installation & Setup
    43
    44### 1. Quick Install Script
    45```bash
    46# Download and install BMAD in any project
    47curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/your-org/bmad-method/main/install.sh | bash
    48
    49# Or manual installation
    50mkdir -p .bmad
    51# Copy template files (see below)
    52```
    53
    54### 2. Initialize BMAD
    55```bash
    56npm run bmad:init
    57# Interactive setup wizard:
    58# - Project type detection
    59# - Framework selection
    60# - Deployment target configuration
    61# - Agent customization
    62```
    63
    64### 3. Core Commands
    65```json
    66{
    67  "scripts": {
    68    "bmad:init": "node .bmad/scripts/bmad-init.js",
    69    "bmad:flatten": "node .bmad/scripts/codebase-flattener.js",
    70    "bmad:story": "node .bmad/scripts/story-generator.js",
    71    "bmad:plan": "node .bmad/scripts/agent-planner.js",
    72    "bmad:deploy": "node .bmad/scripts/deploy-with-context.js"
    73  }
    74}
    75```
    76
    77## Configuration System
    78
    79### bmad-config.json
    80```json
    81{
    82  "projectName": "{{PROJECT_NAME}}",
    83  "projectType": "web-app", // web-app, api, library, microservice
    84  "framework": "express",   // express, react, django, spring, etc.
    85  "language": "javascript", // javascript, python, java, go, etc.
    86  "deploymentTarget": "cloud", // cloud, on-premise, hybrid
    87  "cloudProvider": "aws",   // aws, gcp, azure, railway, vercel
    88  
    89  "features": {
    90    "contextPreservation": true,
    91    "multiAgentPlanning": true,
    92    "automaticDeployment": true,
    93    "testingIntegration": true,
    94    "securityScanning": true
    95  },
    96  
    97  "integrations": {
    98    "cicd": "github-actions", // github-actions, gitlab-ci, jenkins
    99    "monitoring": "prometheus", // prometheus, datadog, newrelic
   100    "databases": ["postgresql"], // postgresql, mongodb, redis
   101    "messageQueues": [], // rabbitmq, kafka, sqs
   102    "apis": [] // stripe, twilio, sendgrid, etc.
   103  },
   104  
   105  "customSettings": {
   106    "maxContextSize": "10MB",
   107    "storyRetention": "6months",
   108    "agentTimeout": "300s"
